01:48:02,356 --> 01:48:03,789
Here was a slaughter

1710
01:48:03,857 --> 01:48:08,089
immeasurably greater than
what happened at Amritsar.

1711
01:48:08,128 --> 01:48:11,620
Can there be anything moral about it?

1712
01:48:13,000 --> 01:48:14,399
Nothing...

1713
01:48:14,468 --> 01:48:16,299
except that it stopped Germany

1714
01:48:16,370 --> 01:48:18,270
from enslaving all of Europe.

1715
01:48:18,338 --> 01:48:23,207
Civil disobedience isn't moral
because it's non-violent.

1716
01:48:23,277 --> 01:48:26,246
Fighting for your country with violence

1717
01:48:26,313 --> 01:48:28,781
can be deeply moral,

1718
01:48:28,882 --> 01:48:34,047
demanding the greatest
sacrifice of all:

1719
01:48:34,154 --> 01:48:36,452
life itself.

1720
01:48:36,523 --> 01:48:39,959
Non-violence is the mask
civil disobedience wears

1721
01:48:40,060 --> 01:48:43,587
to conceal its true face--

1722
01:48:43,664 --> 01:48:46,155
anarchy.

1723
01:48:57,611 --> 01:49:00,375
Gandhi believes one must always act

1724
01:49:00,547 --> 01:49:03,345
with love and respect
for one's opponents,

1725
01:49:03,450 --> 01:49:05,975
even if they are Harvard debaters.

1726
01:49:07,588 --> 01:49:11,524
Gandhi also believes
that lawbreakers must accept

1727
01:49:11,592 --> 01:49:14,857
the legal consequences for their actions.

1728
01:49:14,928 --> 01:49:17,055
Does that sound like anarchy?

